ON STARTUP WE ALWAYS HAVE A SQLITE 

[] GET REQUEST CHECKS FOR DB TYPE
-> IF DB TYPE == SQLITE WE SIMPLY SHOW THE DBCONFIG PATH

ELSE IF THE TYPE IS POSTGRES THEN DEFINETELY WE SHOULD SHOULD HAVE CONFIG.JSON

IF CONFIG.JSON IS MADE ONCE WE DITCH FINDING FROM THE config.db FILE AND ALWAYS LOOK FROM CONFIG.JSON